{{Denmark-tv-stub}}

The '''56th Reserve Infantry Battalion''' (56 Res Inf Bn, or 56 Bn) was an [[Republic of Ireland|Irish]] [[infantry]] [[battalion]] of the [[Reserve Defence Forces]]. 

56 Bn, also known as the Midland Battalion,<ref>[http://www.westmeathindependent.ie/news/roundup/articles/2008/12/05/33850-athlone-army-reservists-excel-in-platoon-assessment-exercise/ "Athlone Army Reservists excel in platoon assessment exercise"], ''Westmeath Independent'', 5 December 2008</ref> was created by the amalgamation on 1 October 2005 of the old 16th Battalion, 17 Bn and parts of 19 Bn of the [[Irish Army]]'s second-line reserve, the ''Fórsa Cosanta Áitiúil'' (FCA), into a reorganised [[Army Reserve (Ireland)|Army Reserve]]. 

56 Bn was abolished in a further 2012 reorganisation of the [[Defence Forces (Ireland)|Defence Forces]].

