The '''flag of [[Mon State]]''' depicts a [[Hamsa (bird)|hamsa]] in the centre of a red background. The current flag was approved by the [[Mon State Hluttaw]] and officially adopted on 8 June 2018.<ref name="bni8618" />

In local legend, the [[Bago, Myanmar|city of Bago]], which was founded by the [[Mon people]], was established on the location where a hamsa sought refuge during a massive flood, hence the adoption of the bird on the flag.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kuipers |first1=Ludo |title=Mon State {{!}} Flag {{!}} Myanmar {{!}} OzOutback |url=https://ozoutback.com.au/Myanmar/flags/slides/21_Mon_State.html |website=ozoutback.com.au |accessdate=9 July 2018}}</ref>

== Former flag ==
Mon State's former flag, used until the adoption of the current flag on 8 June 2018, depicted a hamsa on a dark blue background and had "Mon State" ({{my|မွန်ပြည်နယ်}}) written underneath it.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mon State (Myanmar) |url=https://www.crwflags.com/fotw/flags/mm-mon.html |website=www.crwflags.com |accessdate=9 July 2018}}</ref> The [[flag of Bago Region]] is very similar to the former flag of Mon State, but its hamsa and text have different proportions and designs.

