{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Świdnica |latin = Dioecesis Suidniciensis |local = Diecezja Świdnicka |image = Świdnica - Cathedral.jpg |image_size = 200px |image_alt = |caption = Cathedral of Sts. Paul, Stanislaus and Wenceslaus in [[Świdnica]] |country = [[Poland]] |province = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Wrocław|Wrocław]] |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Wrocław|Wrocław]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |established = 24 February 2004 |cathedral = (''Cathedral of St. Stanislaus and St. Wenceslaus'') |cocathedral = |area_km2 = 4,500 |population = 637,000 |population_as_of = 2014 |catholics = 621,000 |catholics_percent= 97.5 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = [[Ignacy Dec]] |metro_archbishop = [[Józef Kupny]] |coadjutor = |auxiliary_bishops= Adam Bałabuch |website = [http://www.diecezja.swidnica.pl/ Website of the Diocese] }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Świdnica''' ({{lang-la|Suidnicien(sis)}}) is an [[diocese]] located in the city of [[Świdnica]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Wrocław|Wrocław]] in [[Poland]]. In 2013 about 28.7% of the dioceses population attended a church on Sundays regularly according to the church statistics.
==History== The new diocese was created from the combination of 13 deaneries of the Archdiocese of Wroclaw and 8 deaneries of the Diocese of Legnica.
On February 24, 2004, [[Pope John Paul II|John Paul II]] announced the election of [[Świdnica]] (from [[Nysa, Poland|Nysa]], [[Wałbrzych]] and [[Kłodzko]]) as the capital of the new diocese in [[Lower Silesia]].
On March 19, 2008, [[Pope Benedict XVI]] appointed Adam Bałabuch, the first [[auxiliary bishop]] in the diocese.
==Leadership== [[Image:Ignacy Dec.jpg|thumb|Bishop Ignacy Dec]] * [[Bishop]]s of Świdnica (Roman rite): ** Bishop Ignacy Dec (since February 24, 2004)
* Auxilary bishop ** Adam Bałabuch (since March 19, 2008)
