{{Infobox radio station | name = Starr FM | image = | city = [[Accra]] | area = [[Greater Accra Region]] | branding = | slogan = | airdate = 2014 | frequency = 103.5&nbsp;MHz | format = Local news, talk, sports, politics and music | language = [[English language|English]] | power = | erp = | class = | callsign_meaning = | sister_stations =[[Live FM]], [[Kasapa FM]] | owner = <!--Kwabena Duffuor--> [[Excellence In Broadcasting]] | website = {{URL|http://starrfmonline.com/}} }}
'''Starr FM''' is a privately owned urban, lifestyle radio station, which focuses on the delivery of compelling programmes through good music, entertainment/lifestyle-led talk programmes and sports for its target audience and a member of the Excellence In Broadcasting (EIB Network). The radio station is in [[Accra]], the capital of [[Ghana]]. The station is owned by former Ghana Finance Minister [[Kwabena Duffuor]].<ref name="STARRFM">{{cite web | url=http://onlineradiobox.com/gh/starrfm/ | title=Starr FM | publisher=www.onlineradiobox.com | access-date=September 15, 2017}}</ref><ref name="STARR">{{cite web | url=https://www.graphic.com.gh/entertainment/tv-radio/bola-ray-and-co-land-at-new-star-fm.html| title=Bola Ray and co land at new Star FM| publisher=www.graphic.com.gh | access-date=September 15, 2017}}</ref>
