[[Image:Uirlogo.png|thumb|right|UiR symbol]]{{Politics of Andorra}}

'''Unity and Renewal''' ({{lang-ca|Unitat i Renovació}}, UiR) was a local [[political party]] in [[Canillo]], [[Andorra]].

==History==
Although political parties were not legalised until 1993,<ref>Nohlen & Stöver, p153</ref> the party contested the [[Andorran parliamentary election, 1992|1992 elections]] in the [[Canillo]] parish, winning three of the four seats.<ref>[http://hemeroteca.lavanguardia.com/preview/1992/04/13/pagina-13/33519070/pdf.html Government's argument wins absolute majority in Andorra] La Vanguardia, 13 April 1992</ref>

For the [[Andorran parliamentary election, 1997|1997 elections]], it was one of several local parties to ally with the [[Liberal Party of Andorra|Liberal Union]] to run in parish constituencies.<ref name=NS>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen D]] & Stöver P (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p162 {{ISBN|978-3-8329-5609-7}}</ref> The UiR won two seats as the alliance won a total of 16 of the 28 seats in the [[General Council (Andorra)|General Council]],<ref>Nohlen & Stöver, p165</ref> and formed a government under [[Marc Forné Molné]].

